# GitHub weekday save (5 PM)

Remote: https://github.com/antonioj1613-beep/App-expo-tech.git  
Branch: `main`  
Working directory: `App-expo-tech/`

## Schedule

- **Monday–Friday at 17:00** (local time): save all changes to GitHub.
- **Do not save today** unless the user explicitly asks.
- **Skip** if there are no uncommitted changes (no empty commits).

## How to save

From `App-expo-tech/`:

```powershell
.\scripts\save-to-github.ps1
```

The script already:
1. `git add -A`
2. Exits with no commit if `git status --porcelain` is empty
3. Commits with message `Guardado automático YYYY-MM-DD HH:mm`
4. Pushes to `origin main`

## Manual save

Run the same script anytime the user asks to save or push to GitHub.

## Do not

- Push secrets (`.env`, credentials)
- Force-push to `main`
- Commit when the user has not made changes and has not asked for a save
